# Whitelist approach — only ship what the Dockerfile needs to build the wheel
# and a runtime venv. Everything else is excluded by the leading `**`.
**

!pyproject.toml
!uv.lock
!README.md
!LICENSE
!src
!src/**

# Defensive re-excludes (in case any of the whitelisted paths contain noise)
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ipynb_checkpoints
